               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-206-person1747">
                  ROBERT 
                  SLOCOMB
               <interp inst="t18281204-206-person1747" type="surname" value="SLOCOMB"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-206-person1747" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-206-person1747" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Charlotte-street, and am a <rs id="t18281204-206-viclabel1099" type="occupation">tallow-chandler</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-206-victim1745 t18281204-206-viclabel1099"></join>. The prisoner was in my service - I sent him with some goods in my cart to the City-road on the 30th of October about half-past three o'clock - he was gone rather longer than he should have been; I went and found he had delivered the goods and received the money; I went home and found he had not returned; this coat was in the cart, and is my property; I went off next morning and found him at Bristol; I found fifteen sovereigns on him - he said he hoped I would not be hard with him; he said he had the money given him, and he thought he might take it - I paid him 10s. a week and his lodging; I did not tell him to receive the money.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-206-person1748">
                  RICHARD 
                  RICHARDS
               <interp inst="t18281204-206-person1748" type="surname" value="RICHARDS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-206-person1748" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-206-person1748" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. Lloyd. On the 13th of October, I, and the other shopman, paid the prisoner the 16l. in gold, and 5l. 4s. 6d. in copper - the other shopman counted it first, and then I did - it was put on the counter, and the prisoner took it up.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-206-person1749">
                  SAMUEL 
                  TATE
               <interp inst="t18281204-206-person1749" type="surname" value="TATE"></interp>
